CacheStorageDelete.summary:
The delete() method of the interface finds the object matching the cacheName, and if found, deletes the object and returns a {{jsxref("Promise")}} that resolves to true.
If no object is found, it resolves to false.

remarks.para: You can access CacheStorage through the global property.

CacheStorageDelete.returns:
a that resolves to true if the
object is found and deleted, and false otherwise.
